Just because lately there has been a lot of misinformation about Orthodoxy, as a Bulgarian I want to make a few things clear:

- American converts have been some of the most important Orthodox figures of the last century

- Writings of USA converts like Hieromonk Damascene...

... and Seraphim Rose are widely read here and in Serbia, Russia

- In all my life and all discussions about America, never has anyone here said anything negative about Western converts, except that "they face the hardest struggle"

- Native believers are deeply impressed with...

... such stories and we actually respect anyone who chooses himself to join Orthodoxy far more than any cradle believer

- There is no secret spirituality inaccessible to Westerners that we have, life here isnt too different

- The average convert is 200% more pious than a cradle

Basically we love you all and welcome you all and the only people who would try to meme you into believing you are not welcome here is some coping caths/protestants (and catholicism is just as foreign to America as Orthodoxy)
